title: Grateful Dead Live at Capitol Theatre on 1978-11-24
lineage: DAT > WAV transfer:  Playback on Sony PCM-R500 > Neutrik input on Presonus Firebox preamp/A:D > firewire/XP Pro PC > Wavelab 5, recorded as 24 bit/96 KHz WAV > Waves L3 Multimaximizer (mastered to 16 bit/44.1 KHz WAV using hi res CD dither settings) > CDWAV 1.9 (tracking and FLAC encoding) > FLAC (level 8).

reviews.review_text: Thank you very much For uploading this terrific recording and lovely show.
ditto What a magnificent performance and amazing recording......I totally agree with the last reviewer Thad...........keep em comin guys.........and Thank you......for a real good time.........

Spectacular Crystalline highs, A-bomb bass, one of the finest sound-spectrum recordings of the Dead on the entire Archive. Exceptional. This IS the "Way Back Machine," transporting us through time to the Capitol Theatre in Passaiac New Jersey in 1978. Close your eyes and POOF!... Jerry's alive and cooking again. Thank you, Archive. Merry Christmas.
thanks for the memories i know i attended this show, i know i had a good time, but i couldnt remember anything about the quality of the show. thank you archive gods for the memories 4.5

Dead On This Day... I'm two months into a personal project of listening to  Dead shows played on this date in history. Nice way to understand their development over the years. 
I am deeply thankful to everyone who made this Archive possible, from original tapers, to folks like Matthew Vernon and their masterful processing prowess to make even the oldest, grittiest shows a pleasant listening experience.  
This show is the finest, cleanest, full-spectrum recording I've heard yet. Thank you, Matthew!
